==English==

===Alternative spellings===
* '''[[gungho]]'''
* '''[[gung-ho]]'''

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /gʌŋ ˈhəʊ/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /gVN 'h@U/

===Etymology===
World War II; misapplication of Mandarin Chinese ''gonghé'' ([[工]] ''gōng'', work + [[合]] ''hé'', together), an acroym for ''gōngyè hézuòshè'' ([[工業]][[合作社]], [[工业]][[合作社]] Chinese Industrial Cooperative Society).

I believe it is the Chinese Cantonese pronunciation of the phrase, 更好, meaning "better" or "even better".

===Adjective===
'''gung ho'''

# (informal, disapproving) very [[enthusiasm|enthusiastic]] or [[energy|energetic]]
#:''No matter how gung ho you are when you start, you will tire as you become mired in details.''

